Package: compbench
Version: 1.0rc1-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Robin DUBREUIL <robin@dubreuil.pro>
Installed-Size: 37
Depends: python3 (>= 3.6), python3-psutil, xz-utils, pv, btrfs-progs, btrfs-compsize, gdisk, tar, util-linux
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/Robin-DUBREUIL/compbench/
Description: An exhaustive benchmark for Btrfs transparent compression
 Compbench is a comprehensive benchmarking tool for evaluating Btrfs transparent
 compression algorithms. It tests various compression methods (e.g., zstd, lzo, none)
 and levels, with options for repeated tests, forced compression modes, HDD zone testing,
 and synchronized writes. The tool outputs detailed performance metrics and supports CSV export.
